        jTextArea1.setText("A courier management system will help to reduce the day to day hectic manual work of keeping records by automating all the manual work of courier related organizations into computer based\nwork. The main objective of this project is to build a user friendly application which manages courier related information. The system is a multi-user system. The system enables the administrator to keep\nrecords of all the courier senders, receivers, details of the product which is being sent via courier\nservice including the current dispatch status of the package and employees’ information. The product\ndetails include the type of product (document, electronic product, clothes, other), the type of delivery,\ndeliverer’s information, Bill information, Estimate delivery date and location in which service is\navailable. According to weight, product delivery charges will vary. Secondly, the customers make up\nthe other set of users of this system. They can register themselves as customers and can update or\ndelete their details whenever they wish to. The customer can easily avail for the service by booking\ncourier. Once booked, they can check where the dispatch has reached whenever they wish to. Once\nthe dispatch reaches its destination, the status is updated. All the database with a backup is stored into\nthe server of the system. This not only reduces the man power but also increases the efficiency of the\nwork demands. This system will be made using JFrames from Netbeans 8.2 for the frontend and\nPhpMySql for databases in the backend.\n1. Courier is not a common carrier and will accept no liability as such.\n2. All goods or articles are carried or transported and all storage and other services are performed by the Courier subject to these conditions.\n3. The Courier is authorised to deliver the goods at the address given to the Courier by the Customer for that purpose, and without prejudice to any other  method of delivery.\n4. Unless otherwise agreed in writing, the goods are earned at the risk of the Customer and the Courier accepts no responsibility in tort or contract or  otherwise for any loss or destruction of, or damage to, or mis-delivery or  failure to deliver, or delay in delivery of goods either in transit or in  storage, whatever the reason.\n5. The customer pays upon delivery if the goods are just to be collected and  dropped. The Customer can pay using cash.\n");
